==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hemitrope
<hw>Hem"i*trope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hemi-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ to turn: cf. F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧mitrope</ets>.]</ety> <def>Half
turned round; half inverted; <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> having a twinned
structure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemitrope</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hemitrope
<hw>Hem"i*trope</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is hemitropal in
construction; <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> a twin crystal having a
hemitropal structure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemitropy</ent>⟦br⟧
